From: xenium@netcom.com (Jeff Morris)
Subject: Re: linux/msdos networking?
Date: Fri, 5 Nov 1993 16:04:38 GMT

Jesse Montrose (jesse@netcom.com) wrote:
:       Just curious, I've got a spare junker box I'm going to put linux on,
: and I also happen to have a few ethernet cards (ne2000).  Has anyone tried
: hooking a linux box to an msdos box?

I'm running linux on a 386DX/40, and I have DOS/Windows running on another
386DX/40, Ethernet between them. I've been able to use a few different
TCP/IP packages (Novell's Lan Work Place, Netmanage's Chameleon), to telnet 
to the Linux box, and FTP to/from the Linux box. It works swell. 

What I haven't tried yet is setting the DOS/Windows box up as an NFS
client. that should be interesting, and if I can get it to work, I should
be able to put almost all of my hard disk space, CD-ROM and tape drive, in
the Linux box, and be able to access it from either machine. for that
matter, I even moved my modem into my Linux box. I can dial in, dial out,
and do UUCP. When I want to use the modem from DOS, I just telnet to
Linux, and use Linux's Minicom program instead.

Try it, you'll like it!


 - Jeff - xenium@netcom.com


